1
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,969
DOCTOR SHIN

2
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:40,007
THIS IS A FICTIONAL PRODUCTION

3
00:00:40,073 --> 00:00:41,041
ALL NAMES, LOCATIONS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND CASES ARE FICTITIOUS

4
00:00:41,108 --> 00:00:41,975
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH PARENTAL PERMISSION

5
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:42,102
You got through it.

6
00:02:10,597 --> 00:02:12,099
The reason I wanted to see you

7
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:13,800
is about Jin-ju.

8
00:02:14,101 --> 00:02:16,169
You know I've worked with her
for the last few years.

9
00:02:16,937 --> 00:02:19,373
It's time we hold
her memorial service at the temple.

10
00:02:19,439 --> 00:02:20,307
EPISODE 7

11
00:02:20,374 --> 00:02:21,341
She's not dead.

12
00:02:21,408 --> 00:02:22,643
But it seems that she's--

13
00:02:22,709 --> 00:02:24,444
You don't think I know my daughter?

14
00:02:24,511 --> 00:02:25,946
<i>How would he know?</i>

15
00:02:26,013 --> 00:02:27,447
<i>It's not like he even raised her.</i>

16
00:02:28,315 --> 00:02:30,717
She wouldn't just end her life like that.

17
00:02:30,784 --> 00:02:31,952
It's all an act.

18
00:02:32,019 --> 00:02:34,621
Would you write a suicide note
just to put on a show?

19
00:02:34,688 --> 00:02:37,157
There was a sparkle in her eyes.

20
00:02:37,224 --> 00:02:38,425
With eyes like that,

21
00:02:39,426 --> 00:02:40,994
you don't just throw your life away.

22
00:02:42,295 --> 00:02:43,930
<i>Right, and now he's an expert</i>
<i>at reading faces?</i>

23
00:02:46,366 --> 00:02:47,434
You got a cake, too?

24
00:02:55,809 --> 00:02:57,244
Where is this cake from? It's so good.

25
00:02:57,310 --> 00:02:58,478
I'm not telling you.

26
00:02:58,912 --> 00:03:00,180
Just tell me when you want some.

27
00:03:00,247 --> 00:03:01,915
What if I want it every day?

28
00:03:01,982 --> 00:03:03,417
I'll bring it every day.

29
00:03:03,483 --> 00:03:04,785
You have that much free time?

30
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:06,720
I have my secretary and driver.

31
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,525
You should move on from Jin-ju.

32
00:03:13,727 --> 00:03:16,029
Everyone parts ways eventually.

33
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:18,699
I also don't have my parents anymore,

34
00:03:19,232 --> 00:03:20,701
and I'm living just fine.

35
00:03:26,273 --> 00:03:27,841
Jjanji, did you hear that?

36
00:03:28,241 --> 00:03:29,776
We'll take good care of you.

37
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:32,112
With all our love.

38
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:35,949
I can't believe I actually have a puppy.

39
00:03:37,451 --> 00:03:38,418
Thank you.

40
00:03:39,186 --> 00:03:41,254
You made me want to get one too.

41
00:03:41,321 --> 00:03:42,355
I wasn't interested before.

42
00:03:42,823 --> 00:03:44,758
Just let me know if he's ever a bother.

43
00:03:45,726 --> 00:03:47,961
Once I set my heart on something,
I don't change.

44
00:03:48,695 --> 00:03:50,564
I'm not sure
if that's a good thing or a bad thing.

45
00:03:51,665 --> 00:03:53,133
<i>Then his feelings for Momo</i>

46
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,435
<i>won't change either, will they?</i>

47
00:03:58,105 --> 00:03:59,005
Is it a bad thing?

48
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:02,409
I don't know.

49
00:04:03,376 --> 00:04:04,544
So you're saying it's a flaw.

50
00:04:07,481 --> 00:04:09,483
Well, no one's perfect.

51
00:04:12,052 --> 00:04:13,253
What about my flaws?

52
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,521
Tell me, and I'll fix them.

53
00:04:14,855 --> 00:04:16,123
I've never thought about it.

54
00:04:17,424 --> 00:04:18,325
I don't think you have any.

55
00:04:18,859 --> 00:04:19,693
Yeah, you don't.

56
00:04:20,894 --> 00:04:23,430
But don't flaws make us human?

57
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:25,799
So are you saying that I'm human

58
00:04:25,866 --> 00:04:27,434
or that you're not?

59
00:04:27,901 --> 00:04:28,869
You figure it out.

60
00:04:30,303 --> 00:04:31,571
If you're calling me human,

61
00:04:31,638 --> 00:04:33,974
that means I have flaws
worth pointing out.

62
00:04:36,076 --> 00:04:38,111
And you don't think of yourself as human?

63
00:04:38,578 --> 00:04:41,348
Honestly, there are times
I feel less than human.

64
00:04:43,617 --> 00:04:45,552
I had no choice but to live that way.

65
00:04:46,386 --> 00:04:48,789
Nothing ever came easy for me.

66
00:04:49,890 --> 00:04:51,358
I guess I'm my own worst critic.

67
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:54,594
I've always been too hard on myself.

68
00:04:54,661 --> 00:04:56,429
That's not being less than human.

69
00:04:57,130 --> 00:04:58,899
It's not like you were a burden to anyone.

70
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,768
You were just doing your best.

71
00:05:02,769 --> 00:05:05,138
From now on,
take care of yourself for a change.

72
00:05:07,274 --> 00:05:08,441
I know what you mean.

73
00:05:08,842 --> 00:05:13,380
You deserve to be loved
because you're more than worthy.

74
00:07:08,862 --> 00:07:10,263
Would you like an Americano?

75
00:07:10,330 --> 00:07:11,598
I've already had several.

76
00:07:11,831 --> 00:07:15,235
How about a small memorial
for Jin-ju, just ourselves?

77
00:07:22,175 --> 00:07:23,843
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

78
00:07:23,910 --> 00:07:25,211
We'll miss you.

79
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,803
Jin-ju's father claims she's not dead,
so he won't hold the service.

80
00:07:49,869 --> 00:07:50,870
It's unbelievable.

81
00:07:50,937 --> 00:07:52,739
And the police
have already closed the case.

82
00:07:53,606 --> 00:07:55,709
He probably just can't accept it.

83
00:07:57,911 --> 00:07:59,379
Should we just use a memorial tablet?

84
00:08:01,014 --> 00:08:03,516
We should at least
prepare one of her clothes.

85
00:08:05,919 --> 00:08:07,554
I wonder if Momo will come.

86
00:08:42,255 --> 00:08:44,257
BA-RA

87
00:08:49,929 --> 00:08:50,764
Hey, Ba-ra.

88
00:08:53,733 --> 00:08:54,768
Are you free to talk?

89
00:08:54,834 --> 00:08:55,668
Of course.

90
00:08:56,169 --> 00:08:58,471
<i>I talked it over with Mr. Ha,</i>

91
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:02,375
<i>and we're going to hold</i>
<i>a temple memorial service for Jin-ju.</i>

92
00:09:02,442 --> 00:09:03,843
We were hoping you could make it.

93
00:09:04,944 --> 00:09:06,379
<i>My own memorial service?</i>

94
00:09:09,516 --> 00:09:10,550
But no pressure if you can't.

95
00:09:11,785 --> 00:09:12,619
When is it?

96
00:09:12,685 --> 00:09:14,821
Saturday at 2 p.m., Eungyeongsa Temple.

97
00:09:16,289 --> 00:09:18,291
<i>Jin-ju was always good to you, you know.</i>

98
00:09:19,959 --> 00:09:20,794
She really was.

99
00:09:23,263 --> 00:09:24,898
You mean the temple in Gapyeong?

100
00:09:24,964 --> 00:09:25,999
That's the one.

101
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:27,167
I can give you a ride.

102
00:09:29,169 --> 00:09:30,303
So you're coming?

103
00:09:30,937 --> 00:09:31,771
Yeah.

104
00:09:32,672 --> 00:09:34,007
It's for Jin-ju, after all.

105
00:09:37,777 --> 00:09:39,145
Let's head out by noon, then.

106
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:41,915
All right.

107
00:09:42,816 --> 00:09:43,650
Thanks.

108
00:09:44,717 --> 00:09:45,685
Don't mention it.

109
00:09:54,794 --> 00:09:57,831
<i>Have you seen the articles</i>
<i>popping up on all the news sites?</i>

110
00:09:57,897 --> 00:10:00,667
Yeah, I guess the haters
are working overtime.

111
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:02,435
<i>I have to write an article too.</i>

112
00:10:02,502 --> 00:10:03,470
<i>My editor is...</i>

113
00:10:03,536 --> 00:10:05,738
Write whatever you need to. It's okay.

114
00:10:05,805 --> 00:10:07,240
In fact, you could even take it further.

115
00:10:08,842 --> 00:10:11,311
<i>I know everything about Momo.</i>

116
00:10:29,129 --> 00:10:30,230
Why are you flustered?

117
00:10:31,865 --> 00:10:33,066
We're engaged, you know.

118
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:36,302
It was a difficult surgery,
so you need to get a grip.

119
00:10:38,171 --> 00:10:39,072
Okay.

120
00:10:39,672 --> 00:10:41,341
And stop being so careful around me.

121
00:10:43,376 --> 00:10:44,377
Okay.

122
00:11:32,625 --> 00:11:33,459
Open...

123
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:39,532
your eyes.

124
00:12:10,597 --> 00:12:11,698
<i>Dear Lord...</i>

125
00:12:12,465 --> 00:12:14,167
<i>Is this really happening?</i>

126
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:26,012
Yong-jung.

127
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:28,147
We came to get you.

128
00:12:29,082 --> 00:12:30,216
Jjanji!

129
00:12:33,019 --> 00:12:34,120
Aw, you're so cute.

130
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:35,321
It's heavy.

131
00:12:35,388 --> 00:12:36,756
You'll mess up your shoulder with this.

132
00:12:36,823 --> 00:12:38,224
Take my other car today.

133
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:40,393
And give people a reason to talk?

134
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:41,527
Tell them you found your brother.

135
00:12:42,528 --> 00:12:43,896
Let me walk him for a bit.

136
00:12:43,963 --> 00:12:45,465
- You go on ahead.
- Why?

137
00:12:45,531 --> 00:12:47,200
That bag is too heavy.

138
00:12:50,003 --> 00:12:50,837
Let's go.

139
00:12:53,273 --> 00:12:55,275
They say dogs take after their owners.

140
00:12:55,642 --> 00:12:57,410
I wonder which one of us is his owner.

141
00:12:57,477 --> 00:12:59,779
Should we each call his name
and see who he comes to?

142
00:12:59,846 --> 00:13:01,648
No, that'll put him in a tough spot.

143
00:13:03,182 --> 00:13:06,019
I might've been upset
if you'd called Jjanji first.

144
00:13:06,085 --> 00:13:08,921
Come on. You're not that petty.

145
00:13:09,656 --> 00:13:12,225
I'm not petty. I'd just be disappointed.

146
00:13:12,659 --> 00:13:13,493
You're...

147
00:13:14,327 --> 00:13:15,695
as benevolent as the sea.

148
00:13:16,529 --> 00:13:18,097
Spoken like a true journalist.

149
00:13:18,765 --> 00:13:21,167
I doubt kids your age
even know what that means.

150
00:13:21,234 --> 00:13:22,802
Am I sucking up too much today?

151
00:13:23,336 --> 00:13:24,470
You're always welcome to.

152
00:13:26,939 --> 00:13:27,874
Yong-jung.

153
00:13:31,577 --> 00:13:32,412
What was that?

154
00:13:43,122 --> 00:13:47,593
<i>Tonight</i>

155
00:13:48,061 --> 00:13:50,663
<i>I'll send you</i>

156
00:13:51,464 --> 00:13:53,900
<i>The fireflies</i>

157
00:13:55,435 --> 00:13:59,605
<i>From that night</i>

158
00:13:59,972 --> 00:14:02,809
<i>To your window</i>

159
00:14:10,817 --> 00:14:13,086
I don't think I'll ever forget tonight.

160
00:14:15,254 --> 00:14:20,226
<i>I'm telling you</i>

161
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:23,796
<i>That I love you</i>

162
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:30,236
<i>I can recall</i>

163
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,239
<i>The first time</i>

164
00:14:33,973 --> 00:14:36,576
<i>That we met</i>

165
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:38,945
<i>And then</i>

166
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:41,647
<i>Whenever I want</i>

167
00:14:42,315 --> 00:14:45,651
<i>I close my eyes</i>

168
00:14:50,289 --> 00:14:55,228
<i>And go to a place</i>

169
00:14:55,862 --> 00:14:57,663
<i>Far, far away</i>

170
00:15:02,268 --> 00:15:04,337
Sounds like I need to make
more memories with you.

171
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:09,909
It doesn't count
if you're trying to force it.

172
00:15:09,976 --> 00:15:11,477
It wouldn't be forced.

173
00:15:11,778 --> 00:15:14,313
So, were you a good or bad son
to your parents?

174
00:15:16,015 --> 00:15:16,849
A bit of both?

175
00:15:21,521 --> 00:15:22,422
To me,

176
00:15:22,955 --> 00:15:24,824
you're the sweetest man in the world.

177
00:15:26,659 --> 00:15:27,627
I love you.

178
00:15:38,204 --> 00:15:39,238
Jjanji.

179
00:15:39,305 --> 00:15:41,707
Look how she's ignoring my love.

180
00:15:42,308 --> 00:15:44,477
Don't worry, I took it all in.

181
00:15:45,678 --> 00:15:47,346
I'm filled to the brim with love now.

182
00:15:48,581 --> 00:15:50,416
I'm afraid some of it will spill out

183
00:15:50,483 --> 00:15:52,218
if I say even a single word.

184
00:15:57,457 --> 00:15:58,491
What's with the sigh?

185
00:15:58,558 --> 00:16:00,460
This must be how it feels to be a dad.

186
00:16:01,861 --> 00:16:04,130
It's clear that you've never dated.

187
00:16:04,197 --> 00:16:05,331
If you had,

188
00:16:05,398 --> 00:16:07,500
you would've had
another man here instead of me.

189
00:16:09,869 --> 00:16:12,205
No guy in his right mind
would ever let you go.

190
00:16:13,539 --> 00:16:14,874
That kind of sounds like an insult.

191
00:16:15,708 --> 00:16:18,244
I'm telling you
not to flirt with anyone except me.

192
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:29,722
Was I flirting just now?

193
00:16:32,091 --> 00:16:32,925
No.

194
00:16:32,992 --> 00:16:35,862
You said you don't see me
as a woman but a sister.

195
00:16:36,295 --> 00:16:37,830
Is that how you talk to your sister?

196
00:16:39,165 --> 00:16:39,999
That's not--

197
00:16:40,066 --> 00:16:41,734
And what was that
about me ignoring your love?

198
00:16:41,801 --> 00:16:43,970
And how was I flirting just for winking?

199
00:16:44,770 --> 00:16:46,706
To me, it's just a wink,

200
00:16:46,772 --> 00:16:48,908
but to other guys,
it could look like you're flirting.

201
00:16:52,178 --> 00:16:54,046
They're not all
as innocent as I am, you know.

202
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:57,483
Yeah, you're just overflowing
with innocence.

203
00:16:57,783 --> 00:17:00,720
I've had my fill
of your pure, innocent love.

204
00:17:00,786 --> 00:17:03,022
So why don't you go
pour out the rest to Momo?

205
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:10,863
Ba-ra.

206
00:17:15,067 --> 00:17:16,369
Are you really that upset?

207
00:17:17,937 --> 00:17:18,938
I'm sorry.

208
00:17:19,005 --> 00:17:21,107
I never had any sisters, so I didn't know.

209
00:17:21,173 --> 00:17:23,309
Didn't you say you dated older girls?

210
00:17:23,376 --> 00:17:25,044
- Just twice.
- And what about Momo?

211
00:17:26,312 --> 00:17:27,980
That was just a one-sided crush.

212
00:17:29,982 --> 00:17:31,784
At the Appreciation Night last year,

213
00:17:32,685 --> 00:17:34,720
was Momo really that captivating?

214
00:17:35,788 --> 00:17:37,390
That you're still not over her?

215
00:17:38,524 --> 00:17:40,326
What did you like so much about her?

216
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:42,428
Was it her looks?

217
00:17:43,396 --> 00:17:44,530
Or her dance skills?

218
00:17:45,364 --> 00:17:46,198
It was just...

219
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,569
was like an electric shock.

220
00:17:51,337 --> 00:17:52,171
A kind of...

221
00:17:54,874 --> 00:17:56,142
thrill.

222
00:17:57,376 --> 00:17:58,344
In your heart?

223
00:17:59,712 --> 00:18:00,546
Or your body?

224
00:18:01,814 --> 00:18:03,316
If I hadn't had any self-control...

225
00:18:05,785 --> 00:18:06,819
I would've held her.

226
00:18:08,487 --> 00:18:10,022
Or grabbed her hand and ran away with her.

227
00:18:11,257 --> 00:18:12,658
It was that intense?

228
00:18:13,793 --> 00:18:15,328
I can't hide anything from you.

229
00:18:16,662 --> 00:18:18,030
I think of her

230
00:18:19,532 --> 00:18:21,133
when I wake up in the morning

231
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:23,869
and when I go to bed.

232
00:18:26,539 --> 00:18:28,541
Then you should
just tell her how you feel.

233
00:18:29,008 --> 00:18:30,343
And betray Ju-sin?

234
00:18:30,409 --> 00:18:31,811
They're not married yet.

235
00:18:31,877 --> 00:18:34,213
I can't live my life
just following my heart.

236
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:36,716
Imagine the world if everyone did that.

237
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:38,884
It'll be complete chaos
with no ethics or morals.

238
00:18:38,951 --> 00:18:39,952
Then what if...

239
00:18:42,355 --> 00:18:44,323
What if she and Dr. Shin broke up?

240
00:18:46,158 --> 00:18:47,093
What would you do?

241
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:53,099
Then I could be honest.

242
00:18:55,434 --> 00:18:56,702
Without a second thought?

243
00:18:56,769 --> 00:18:57,903
What else would matter?

244
00:18:59,772 --> 00:19:00,940
When you really like someone,

245
00:19:01,741 --> 00:19:03,376
you don't need reasons or conditions.

246
00:19:05,911 --> 00:19:07,279
<i>If only that person...</i>

247
00:19:08,547 --> 00:19:09,582
<i>were me.</i>

248
00:19:11,584 --> 00:19:12,818
He's pooping.

249
00:19:37,476 --> 00:19:38,377
Go home and wait.

250
00:19:40,379 --> 00:19:41,580
I mean Momo's in Cheongdam-dong.

251
00:19:41,647 --> 00:19:42,982
Stay away from your old place.

252
00:19:45,151 --> 00:19:46,118
Okay.

253
00:19:50,289 --> 00:19:51,924
Kim Jin-ju is dead to the world now.

254
00:19:52,925 --> 00:19:54,694
Be extra careful when you're around Ba-ra.

255
00:19:55,528 --> 00:19:57,763
It's not just part of her job.
She's naturally perceptive.

256
00:19:58,731 --> 00:19:59,565
<i>You're right.</i>

257
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:02,668
I didn't think
we should just jump into this.

258
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:04,570
And you'd need time to prepare.

259
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,524
<i>From now on,</i>

260
00:20:25,591 --> 00:20:27,326
<i>I'm going to love you, God.</i>

261
00:20:48,814 --> 00:20:49,648
Hello?

262
00:20:50,015 --> 00:20:50,916
<i>This is Paul Kim.</i>

263
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:52,752
<i>You bought one of my paintings--</i>

264
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:54,120
Yes, Mr. Kim.

265
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:57,456
I hung it up at my place,
and it looks absolutely perfect.

266
00:20:57,523 --> 00:20:58,591
<i>I'm glad to hear it.</i>

267
00:20:58,657 --> 00:21:01,260
<i>Well, the reason I'm calling is</i>

268
00:21:01,327 --> 00:21:03,996
<i>I saw on the news</i>
<i>that Ms. Kim Jin-ju is missing...</i>

269
00:21:04,063 --> 00:21:06,232
Wait, do you know Jin-ju?

270
00:21:06,298 --> 00:21:07,266
<i>Yes.</i>

271
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:08,801
<i>It's a bit of a long story.</i>

272
00:21:08,868 --> 00:21:11,303
You said your studio
is in Yangpyeong, right?

273
00:21:11,370 --> 00:21:12,571
<i>I'm in Seoul right now.</i>

274
00:21:13,005 --> 00:21:14,440
Where in Seoul?

275
00:21:14,507 --> 00:21:16,242
Why don't you come over?

276
00:21:16,308 --> 00:21:17,543
<i>Would that be okay?</i>

277
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:18,778
Of course.

278
00:21:18,844 --> 00:21:21,046
You could also see your piece on my wall.

279
00:21:22,081 --> 00:21:23,983
Oh, my. Then what happened?

280
00:21:24,049 --> 00:21:26,719
We did a DNA test, and it wasn't a match.

281
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:29,054
I also have something to tell you.

282
00:21:29,121 --> 00:21:31,056
I met Jin-ju's birth father.

283
00:21:32,324 --> 00:21:33,926
- You did?
- Yes.

284
00:21:34,593 --> 00:21:35,427
Well...

285
00:21:35,761 --> 00:21:37,930
the articles didn't go into detail,

286
00:21:38,531 --> 00:21:40,966
but I think he's the reason
she did such a thing.

287
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:47,039
AN-HUI, KIM JIN-JU, YONG-JUNG

288
00:21:57,817 --> 00:21:59,718
I guess the passcode changed.

289
00:21:59,785 --> 00:22:02,888
You must be here to get things for Jin-ju.

290
00:22:02,955 --> 00:22:04,190
No.

291
00:22:04,256 --> 00:22:06,692
I need some of her clothes
for her memorial service.

292
00:22:08,227 --> 00:22:09,962
Where is the service held?

293
00:22:10,029 --> 00:22:11,730
At Eungyeongsa Temple in Gapyeong.

294
00:22:12,798 --> 00:22:13,899
It's all nonsense.

295
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:16,669
You're all in on it together, aren't you?

296
00:22:16,735 --> 00:22:18,571
You have to accept the reality.

297
00:22:18,637 --> 00:22:20,372
- I know it's hard--
- Accept what?

298
00:22:22,441 --> 00:22:23,943
You tell that daughter of mine

299
00:22:24,210 --> 00:22:25,945
that I'll find her no matter what.

300
00:22:26,946 --> 00:22:28,013
Please, just one outfit.

301
00:22:44,864 --> 00:22:47,366
<i>I can't believe I'm in Momo's seat.</i>

302
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:22,034
You look so elegant.

303
00:23:31,176 --> 00:23:34,847
I went to get her clothes,
but her father wouldn't let me in.

304
00:23:35,848 --> 00:23:37,082
Is he just living there now?

305
00:23:37,149 --> 00:23:38,317
Yeah.

306
00:23:38,384 --> 00:23:41,086
He even did a DNA test,
so there's nothing we can say.

307
00:23:41,153 --> 00:23:42,421
It's technically his daughter's place.

308
00:23:43,055 --> 00:23:45,824
How did he do a DNA test without her?

309
00:23:45,891 --> 00:23:47,493
He used her toothbrush.

310
00:23:47,559 --> 00:23:48,727
Apparently, it was a match.

311
00:23:49,361 --> 00:23:51,563
Mr. Ha confirmed everything too.

312
00:24:01,073 --> 00:24:03,008
Whenever it was sunny,

313
00:24:03,075 --> 00:24:04,944
Jin-ju always wanted
to go to the botanical gardens.

314
00:24:06,745 --> 00:24:07,947
I just can't believe it.

315
00:24:08,814 --> 00:24:10,783
She was always obsessed
with living her best life.

316
00:24:13,686 --> 00:24:14,520
Obsessed?

317
00:24:16,255 --> 00:24:17,856
You know she had many things
she wanted to do.

318
00:24:19,892 --> 00:24:22,394
<i>If you knew all that,</i>
<i>why were you so cold to me?</i>

319
00:24:23,462 --> 00:24:24,863
- I need coffee.
- Okay.

320
00:24:26,332 --> 00:24:28,200
Would I have to give a monetary gift?

321
00:24:28,267 --> 00:24:30,069
I think so. I brought some.

322
00:24:30,135 --> 00:24:31,603
Why? Do you feel like it's a waste?

323
00:24:32,438 --> 00:24:33,839
I don't have to go in, do I?

324
00:24:34,673 --> 00:24:36,942
After all those years together,
you won't even go in?

325
00:24:50,389 --> 00:24:51,623
KIM JIN-JU

326
00:24:56,095 --> 00:24:57,663
<i>Of all the pictures they could've used...</i>

327
00:24:58,497 --> 00:24:59,631
<i>So tacky.</i>

328
00:25:14,313 --> 00:25:17,916
MINJIN CHURCH

329
00:25:17,983 --> 00:25:19,418
PLEASE WRITE DOWN
THE NAME AND DATE OF BIRTH

330
00:25:19,485 --> 00:25:20,853
BABY BOX

331
00:25:26,091 --> 00:25:28,460
Jin-ju, you've had this
since you were a baby.

332
00:25:46,945 --> 00:25:47,780
Hey, you.

333
00:25:48,047 --> 00:25:48,881
Hey!

334
00:25:49,114 --> 00:25:50,049
I said look at me.

335
00:27:37,322 --> 00:27:40,692
What was your relationship
to the deceased?

336
00:27:41,059 --> 00:27:42,427
She was my stylist.

337
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:45,564
A very devout monk
was in charge of the ceremony.

338
00:27:45,631 --> 00:27:47,232
I'm sure her soul was guided peacefully.

339
00:27:47,833 --> 00:27:48,667
Excuse me.

340
00:27:49,234 --> 00:27:50,969
Mr. Park is leaving now.

341
00:27:51,837 --> 00:27:52,771
One moment, please.

342
00:27:53,205 --> 00:27:54,039
Of course.

343
00:28:00,979 --> 00:28:01,813
Not even a single tear?

344
00:28:03,048 --> 00:28:04,950
You grew up together in the orphanage.

345
00:28:06,985 --> 00:28:09,488
It still doesn't feel real to me either.

346
00:28:10,155 --> 00:28:11,790
The human heart is a funny thing.

347
00:28:12,224 --> 00:28:14,793
Since Jin-ju's father
insists she isn't dead,

348
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:16,562
and it's not like we saw a body,

349
00:28:17,629 --> 00:28:19,998
it makes you feel like
she could be alive somewhere.

350
00:28:20,065 --> 00:28:22,734
All the signs say she fell into the ocean.
There's nothing to confirm.

351
00:28:24,136 --> 00:28:25,337
That's true.

352
00:28:25,771 --> 00:28:27,773
Anyway, it's such a shame.
She was so young.

353
00:28:28,407 --> 00:28:30,609
I don't think she ever even got to
experience real love...

354
00:28:31,076 --> 00:28:32,544
<i>I'm in love now</i>

355
00:28:32,945 --> 00:28:34,379
<i>with Dr. Shin.</i>

356
00:28:39,518 --> 00:28:41,820
I found a restaurant nearby
with good reviews.

357
00:28:41,887 --> 00:28:42,888
Let's eat before we go.

358
00:28:42,955 --> 00:28:44,323
We have other plans.

359
00:28:45,023 --> 00:28:48,293
A friend invited me to her house,
and I told her you'd be coming too.

360
00:28:49,861 --> 00:28:53,765
I called you because
Jin-ju worked for your company.

361
00:28:53,832 --> 00:28:55,667
I was so shocked too.

362
00:28:56,702 --> 00:28:59,171
I was really hoping she was my daughter.

363
00:28:59,238 --> 00:29:01,073
I see.

364
00:29:01,139 --> 00:29:02,140
What a small world.

365
00:29:03,008 --> 00:29:05,510
That's how it is in Korea.
Everyone knows everyone.

366
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:06,411
Are you leaving?

367
00:29:07,045 --> 00:29:08,847
Yes, I should let you get some rest.

368
00:29:08,914 --> 00:29:10,649
This is relaxing for me.

369
00:29:10,716 --> 00:29:12,451
Next time you're in Seoul, call me.

370
00:29:12,517 --> 00:29:14,086
Do you ever come to Yangpyeong?

371
00:29:17,823 --> 00:29:19,157
Is one ceremony enough?

372
00:29:19,391 --> 00:29:22,427
A very devout monk performed the rites
with the utmost sincerity.

373
00:29:24,997 --> 00:29:27,899
Please let me prepare
something simple for us to eat.

374
00:29:27,966 --> 00:29:29,067
Oh, let's just eat out--

375
00:29:29,134 --> 00:29:30,669
There's no place to eat out around here.

376
00:29:31,803 --> 00:29:34,072
I'm a pretty decent cook.

377
00:29:35,507 --> 00:29:36,808
As for the wine...

378
00:29:37,442 --> 00:29:38,277
Should we have some?

379
00:29:40,145 --> 00:29:41,313
We should, on a day like today.

380
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:43,515
- We'll do the pairing.
- Very well.

381
00:29:45,817 --> 00:29:48,287
We could have just eaten with Mr. Ha.

382
00:29:48,353 --> 00:29:50,088
I wanted to talk, just the two of us.

383
00:29:51,123 --> 00:29:53,292
Honestly, he talks way too much.

384
00:29:53,992 --> 00:29:54,826
It's exhausting.

385
00:29:56,595 --> 00:29:58,964
I must have grown really fond of Jin-ju.

386
00:29:59,665 --> 00:30:01,600
I just suddenly burst into tears.

387
00:30:02,501 --> 00:30:04,269
I've gotten weaker since Mom passed away.

388
00:30:07,005 --> 00:30:10,275
I'm just glad you pulled yourself together
and didn't fall apart.

389
00:30:10,776 --> 00:30:13,211
I figured you'd want some space,
so I didn't call.

390
00:30:13,712 --> 00:30:16,214
But you know I was always
worried about you, right?

391
00:30:18,417 --> 00:30:19,251
Yeah.

392
00:30:21,620 --> 00:30:22,688
What's your salary?

393
00:30:23,989 --> 00:30:24,890
About 50 million won?

394
00:30:29,928 --> 00:30:33,398
After taxes and putting some into savings,
my actual pay isn't that much.

395
00:30:33,999 --> 00:30:34,933
I need your help.

396
00:30:36,535 --> 00:30:37,836
Anything.

397
00:30:37,903 --> 00:30:39,838
Quit your job and come work for me.

398
00:30:42,407 --> 00:30:43,241
What do you say?

399
00:30:44,176 --> 00:30:45,444
But you have Mr. Oh.

400
00:30:45,911 --> 00:30:47,079
He's just my business manager.

401
00:30:47,646 --> 00:30:50,349
I don't want anyone else.
I want you by my side.

402
00:30:52,117 --> 00:30:54,553
I'll double your salary. Even triple it.

403
00:30:55,954 --> 00:30:57,489
It's not about the salary...

404
00:30:57,556 --> 00:30:58,990
You said you were worried about me.

405
00:31:01,793 --> 00:31:03,061
Do you need me that much?

406
00:31:03,995 --> 00:31:04,830
Yes.

407
00:31:06,565 --> 00:31:09,634
If someone I cared about asked me to,
I'd quit acting in a heartbeat.

408
00:31:13,472 --> 00:31:14,473
I'll think about it.

409
00:31:15,006 --> 00:31:16,942
That's just a nice way of saying no.

410
00:31:17,542 --> 00:31:18,377
Am I wrong?

411
00:31:20,112 --> 00:31:23,882
My superiors depend on me,
so it's hard to just quit out of the blue.

412
00:31:24,549 --> 00:31:25,984
And it was my dream
to become a journalist.

413
00:31:26,985 --> 00:31:28,720
Sure, it is a great career.

414
00:31:28,987 --> 00:31:32,958
But what's next for you?
Becoming an old editorial writer?

415
00:31:33,992 --> 00:31:37,429
Isn't being a gallery director
better than some old editorial writer?

416
00:31:37,496 --> 00:31:38,630
Plus, there's no retirement age.

417
00:31:39,998 --> 00:31:43,568
Help me get settled for a few years,
and the gallery is yours.

418
00:31:44,002 --> 00:31:46,772
You have so many connections
in the art and literature worlds.

419
00:31:49,875 --> 00:31:51,410
Ba-ra's running late.

420
00:32:01,319 --> 00:32:02,921
Don't take too long to think about it.

421
00:32:03,989 --> 00:32:04,823
Okay.

422
00:32:05,424 --> 00:32:06,258
Bye.

423
00:32:07,426 --> 00:32:08,827
Thanks, anyway.

424
00:32:09,861 --> 00:32:11,830
I'll take that as a yes, then?

425
00:32:14,132 --> 00:32:15,500
I envy you.

426
00:32:16,234 --> 00:32:17,302
Why?

427
00:32:17,369 --> 00:32:19,604
You're so loved by everyone.

428
00:32:19,671 --> 00:32:21,273
<i>And you have Yong-jung's love.</i>

429
00:32:22,207 --> 00:32:24,009
Things aren't always what they seem.

430
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:08,420
GEUM BA-RA

431
00:33:10,755 --> 00:33:12,357
<i>Hey.</i>

432
00:33:12,424 --> 00:33:13,825
I'm at your front door with Jjanji.

433
00:33:14,326 --> 00:33:15,160
<i>You're here?</i>

434
00:33:16,027 --> 00:33:17,796
<i>The code's the same as yours.</i>

435
00:33:20,432 --> 00:33:21,566
Have you been drinking?

436
00:33:23,568 --> 00:33:24,769
With Momo.

437
00:33:26,872 --> 00:33:29,808
Now that I'm home,
it's starting to hit me.

438
00:33:32,611 --> 00:33:33,745
Jjanji.

439
00:33:37,916 --> 00:33:39,885
A last-minute workout
came up for tomorrow.

440
00:33:41,219 --> 00:33:42,354
How much did you drink?

441
00:33:42,821 --> 00:33:43,822
Just a wine pairing.

442
00:33:44,155 --> 00:33:45,390
Six glasses.

443
00:33:45,457 --> 00:33:46,625
Yeah, that'll do it.

444
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:49,728
How was the ceremony?

445
00:33:50,395 --> 00:33:51,796
It went well.

446
00:33:56,334 --> 00:33:57,168
Drink this.

447
00:33:58,169 --> 00:33:59,004
You can leave it.

448
00:34:07,879 --> 00:34:08,713
What's wrong?

449
00:34:09,548 --> 00:34:10,382
Feeling sick?

450
00:34:10,949 --> 00:34:12,484
Yeah, a little nauseous.

451
00:34:12,551 --> 00:34:15,220
You should go.
I don't want you to see me like this.

452
00:34:15,287 --> 00:34:16,221
Why not?

453
00:34:16,421 --> 00:34:17,956
You must have seen Momo, right?

454
00:34:18,924 --> 00:34:19,758
Yeah.

455
00:34:20,292 --> 00:34:21,326
Should I call her back?

456
00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:22,928
She can't have gone far.

457
00:34:23,995 --> 00:34:25,363
Go inside and lie down properly.

458
00:34:41,913 --> 00:34:42,847
Can I stay?

459
00:34:44,449 --> 00:34:45,283
Why?

460
00:34:45,350 --> 00:34:47,185
I feel like I should be here for you.

461
00:34:47,252 --> 00:34:48,153
You seem troubled.

462
00:34:49,888 --> 00:34:51,056
Is it that obvious?

463
00:34:51,623 --> 00:34:53,592
Tell me everything.
Get it all off your chest.

464
00:34:54,559 --> 00:34:55,594
I don't want to.

465
00:34:56,227 --> 00:34:57,762
I don't hide anything from you.

466
00:34:58,663 --> 00:34:59,497
I'm hurt.

467
00:35:01,666 --> 00:35:03,068
That's my line.

468
00:35:03,635 --> 00:35:04,636
What do you mean?

469
00:35:05,604 --> 00:35:08,740
There's a difference between hiding things
and not opening up.

470
00:35:08,807 --> 00:35:10,475
So you're not gonna open up?

471
00:35:10,809 --> 00:35:12,310
To me, of all people?

472
00:35:12,744 --> 00:35:14,079
With your bold personality?

473
00:35:15,046 --> 00:35:15,914
Me, bold?

474
00:35:17,248 --> 00:35:18,750
That's just how it looks.

475
00:35:20,785 --> 00:35:23,021
I'm not hurt.

476
00:35:24,222 --> 00:35:25,056
Really?

477
00:35:26,992 --> 00:35:29,260
You would've passed out on the couch
if I weren't here.

478
00:35:29,327 --> 00:35:31,096
No. I have to wash up before I sleep.

479
00:35:31,529 --> 00:35:33,298
I'll get going then. Go wash up.

480
00:35:35,467 --> 00:35:36,768
But you said you'd stay.

481
00:35:42,674 --> 00:35:44,776
All right. I'll sleep here with Jjanji.

482
00:35:46,411 --> 00:35:47,245
Jjanji.

483
00:35:49,814 --> 00:35:52,350
Would you be leaving at dawn
after just a few hours of sleep?

484
00:35:52,417 --> 00:35:55,553
Yes. There's a business meeting
I have to attend.

485
00:35:59,324 --> 00:36:00,558
Do you have any medicine?

486
00:36:00,625 --> 00:36:01,459
Nope.

487
00:36:02,427 --> 00:36:05,530
Momo and I were catching up over drinks.

488
00:36:05,597 --> 00:36:07,065
I don't want to sober up.

489
00:36:10,535 --> 00:36:12,537
You want to know
what we talked about, don't you?

490
00:36:17,409 --> 00:36:19,310
You should stock the fridge
with some food.

491
00:36:19,377 --> 00:36:21,212
I'll pick Jjanji up tomorrow evening.

492
00:36:21,279 --> 00:36:22,914
And call me anytime you need me.

493
00:37:12,530 --> 00:37:13,765
It's pretty, right?

494
00:37:13,832 --> 00:37:15,133
Where'd you get this?

495
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:16,801
What do you mean?

496
00:37:17,368 --> 00:37:18,837
I bought it for you, of course.

497
00:37:23,274 --> 00:37:24,109
With what money?

498
00:37:24,476 --> 00:37:25,777
From the old lady who sponsors me.

499
00:37:26,377 --> 00:37:27,746
She doesn’t like being called old, though.

500
00:37:28,613 --> 00:37:29,581
You wear it.

501
00:37:30,281 --> 00:37:32,050
It looks prettier on you.

502
00:37:36,187 --> 00:37:37,589
Come here, come to Grandma.

503
00:37:38,223 --> 00:37:40,058
I wish we could grow our hair out.

504
00:37:41,526 --> 00:37:43,828
The first thing I'll do after we move out
is let my hair grow.

505
00:37:44,763 --> 00:37:45,597
Me too.

506
00:37:50,235 --> 00:37:52,837
Do you know the song called <i>Mom?</i>

507
00:37:54,005 --> 00:37:54,839
No.

508
00:37:55,774 --> 00:37:57,842
Last night,

509
00:37:58,910 --> 00:38:00,812
Su-bin was crying to that song.

510
00:38:03,214 --> 00:38:04,048
"Mom."

511
00:38:05,850 --> 00:38:07,652
I wonder what it feels like
to call your mom.

512
00:38:14,058 --> 00:38:16,294
Want to close our eyes
and pretend to call our moms?

513
00:38:16,761 --> 00:38:17,729
How?

514
00:38:19,030 --> 00:38:19,864
Just close them.

515
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:23,735
I'll call out, and you answer.

516
00:38:26,704 --> 00:38:27,705
Mom.

517
00:38:31,509 --> 00:38:32,343
Mom?

518
00:38:33,745 --> 00:38:34,579
Yes?

519
00:38:36,147 --> 00:38:37,048
Your turn.

520
00:38:40,418 --> 00:38:41,419
Go on.

521
00:38:43,421 --> 00:38:44,923
Mom.

522
00:38:46,090 --> 00:38:47,759
Why did you make your sister cry?

523
00:38:48,459 --> 00:38:50,461
She's not my sister. We're friends.

524
00:38:50,528 --> 00:38:51,963
Oh my, how old are you?

525
00:38:52,630 --> 00:38:53,765
We're 12.

526
00:38:53,832 --> 00:38:55,533
Then why is she so small?

527
00:38:56,234 --> 00:38:57,502
She doesn't eat much.

528
00:38:57,569 --> 00:38:59,404
You must eat well to grow big.

529
00:38:59,470 --> 00:39:00,605
Don't be a picky eater.

530
00:39:01,206 --> 00:39:02,774
I'll buy you a donut.

531
00:39:02,841 --> 00:39:04,642
You're such a good friend.

532
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:08,313
<i>I was so good to her.</i>

533
00:39:09,147 --> 00:39:10,715
<i>And all she worries about is Momo.</i>

534
00:39:15,787 --> 00:39:16,921
GEUM BA-RA

535
00:39:16,988 --> 00:39:18,690
<i>Yong-jung, can you talk right now?</i>

536
00:39:21,759 --> 00:39:22,594
Hello?

537
00:39:23,161 --> 00:39:23,995
<i>Yong-jung.</i>

538
00:39:25,063 --> 00:39:25,930
Yeah?

539
00:39:25,997 --> 00:39:27,899
<i>Momo asked me to quit my job</i>

540
00:39:28,366 --> 00:39:29,701
<i>and work for her.</i>

541
00:39:31,536 --> 00:39:32,370
She did?

542
00:39:33,137 --> 00:39:34,405
But I'm not going to.

543
00:39:36,307 --> 00:39:37,809
That's the right move, isn't it?

544
00:39:39,077 --> 00:39:40,545
<i>You worked hard to become a journalist.</i>

545
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:43,514
Right.

546
00:39:43,581 --> 00:39:45,216
I'm so proud of you.

547
00:39:46,451 --> 00:39:48,019
<i>Is that why you adore me?</i>

548
00:39:49,520 --> 00:39:50,355
Do I?

549
00:39:51,055 --> 00:39:52,423
<i>Or was it all in my head?</i>

550
00:39:53,091 --> 00:39:54,559
We're in love.

551
00:39:55,260 --> 00:39:56,928
<i>It's more than just adoration.</i>

552
00:39:59,030 --> 00:40:01,266
Don't say things like that
in front of others.

553
00:40:01,332 --> 00:40:02,667
They'll misunderstand.

554
00:40:02,734 --> 00:40:04,202
Does it matter if they do?

555
00:40:05,637 --> 00:40:06,471
<i>Bye.</i>

556
00:40:07,472 --> 00:40:08,306
I love you.

557
00:40:08,706 --> 00:40:09,540
Good night.

558
00:40:10,208 --> 00:40:11,209
<i>You too.</i>

559
00:40:21,719 --> 00:40:24,656
I endured everything just for her.

560
00:40:34,065 --> 00:40:36,267
You don't know a thing about me.

561
00:40:48,780 --> 00:40:50,515
Have your driver go home.
I'll give you a ride.

562
00:41:15,673 --> 00:41:17,008
Your limit is three glasses of wine.

563
00:41:17,875 --> 00:41:18,876
Don't drink more than that.

564
00:41:45,503 --> 00:41:46,871
Are you still not comfortable with me?

565
00:42:02,286 --> 00:42:03,521
You look good in black.

566
00:42:06,190 --> 00:42:07,025
Are you mute?

567
00:42:08,526 --> 00:42:09,360
Say something.

568
00:42:11,229 --> 00:42:15,500
About those two nurses who can't speak...

569
00:42:16,634 --> 00:42:17,535
Are they siblings?

570
00:42:18,002 --> 00:42:19,103
No.

571
00:42:19,170 --> 00:42:20,171
What makes you say that?

572
00:42:21,239 --> 00:42:22,840
When they came to the orphanage,

573
00:42:22,907 --> 00:42:25,209
my father found out they were both mute.

574
00:42:26,177 --> 00:42:27,712
So he had them cared for at our home.

575
00:42:29,814 --> 00:42:30,815
We basically raised them.

576
00:42:31,682 --> 00:42:34,652
You are truly an admirable man.

577
00:42:35,053 --> 00:42:37,789
They always do as I ask
to repay for that kindness.

578
00:42:38,890 --> 00:42:40,391
As they should.

579
00:42:40,658 --> 00:42:41,993
How much does Ba-ra drink?

580
00:42:44,562 --> 00:42:46,264
She had the same wine pairing with me.

581
00:42:46,898 --> 00:42:50,234
And where did you learn
your dining etiquette?

582
00:42:50,902 --> 00:42:52,470
I learned it from Mr. Ha.

583
00:42:53,671 --> 00:42:56,040
He often took me to high-end restaurants.

584
00:42:56,107 --> 00:42:58,342
You have an appointment
with Attorney Kim on Monday at two.

585
00:42:59,577 --> 00:43:01,279
Make sure to review carefully
before you sign.

586
00:43:04,916 --> 00:43:07,118
It's a good thing
Momo's signature is simple.

587
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:24,702
She's not dead.

588
00:43:25,736 --> 00:43:27,071
You're at death's door,

589
00:43:27,672 --> 00:43:29,407
and you don't leave a single photo?

590
00:44:15,319 --> 00:44:17,955
Oh my, you look so good.

591
00:44:18,623 --> 00:44:20,057
I haven't even put it on yet.

592
00:44:28,432 --> 00:44:29,534
I smell food.

593
00:44:34,272 --> 00:44:37,175
The actress is starving,
and you're stinking up the place.

594
00:44:38,476 --> 00:44:39,544
I was just hungry.

595
00:44:39,610 --> 00:44:40,578
And I'm not?

596
00:44:40,645 --> 00:44:42,113
Weren't you just snacking?

597
00:44:45,216 --> 00:44:46,717
You want people gawking at me?

598
00:44:51,489 --> 00:44:52,657
My eyes look so tired.

599
00:44:52,723 --> 00:44:54,192
Didn't get much sleep again?

600
00:44:54,258 --> 00:44:55,860
I shot a commercial until dawn.

601
00:44:55,927 --> 00:44:57,195
It's a good problem to have.

602
00:44:57,261 --> 00:44:59,130
You really have it all.

603
00:44:59,564 --> 00:45:01,432
Except for a Prince Charming.

604
00:45:01,866 --> 00:45:04,402
There are princes all over the world
just waiting to be picked.

605
00:45:05,369 --> 00:45:06,437
You didn't take the ice out?

606
00:45:08,005 --> 00:45:09,507
You know I only take three ice cubes.

607
00:45:11,042 --> 00:45:13,211
You still don't know that
after four months?

608
00:46:07,932 --> 00:46:09,133
You bitch.

609
00:46:38,963 --> 00:46:41,132
Don't you think
Ba-ra's too clever for her own good?

610
00:46:41,766 --> 00:46:42,900
No.

611
00:46:42,967 --> 00:46:44,068
What's bad about that?

612
00:46:45,503 --> 00:46:46,804
You don't understand women, do you?

613
00:46:47,772 --> 00:46:49,273
I guess not as well as you do.

614
00:46:50,007 --> 00:46:52,910
But you can't hide
a person's true character or their vibe.

615
00:46:53,644 --> 00:46:56,280
Besides, I don't see Ba-ra as a woman.

616
00:46:56,347 --> 00:46:57,648
She's like a little sister to me.

617
00:46:57,715 --> 00:46:59,617
But would Ba-ra feel the same way?

618
00:47:00,685 --> 00:47:02,386
I've known her since she was 11.

619
00:47:02,787 --> 00:47:03,954
But not the whole time.

620
00:47:04,255 --> 00:47:05,389
People don't change.

621
00:47:06,590 --> 00:47:08,259
They say you have to be reborn to change.

622
00:47:08,926 --> 00:47:11,162
If that were true,
everyone would've been reborn.

623
00:47:11,228 --> 00:47:12,863
But that doesn't mean everyone's good now.

624
00:47:14,665 --> 00:47:16,067
A great monk once said this.

625
00:47:17,168 --> 00:47:19,170
People only change
through spiritual training.

626
00:47:20,171 --> 00:47:22,773
Even if you're reborn 10,000 times,

627
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:24,475
you won't change
without spiritual training.

628
00:47:25,376 --> 00:47:27,178
Other than the fact
that Ba-ra's an orphan...

629
00:47:28,112 --> 00:47:29,480
Which isn't a flaw.

630
00:47:29,547 --> 00:47:30,881
It's not her fault.

631
00:47:32,850 --> 00:47:35,886
She has a good heart
and carries herself well.

632
00:47:36,387 --> 00:47:37,822
Everything she does is sweet.

633
00:47:39,857 --> 00:47:40,691
Anyway,

634
00:47:41,592 --> 00:47:43,961
I just hope you don't marry her.

635
00:47:44,028 --> 00:47:44,895
Don't worry.

636
00:47:45,529 --> 00:47:47,365
Just don't be prejudiced against her.

637
00:47:54,305 --> 00:47:58,042
- Good shot!
- Nice! Good shot!

638
00:48:05,216 --> 00:48:07,918
- What's with the rain?
- Get an umbrella.

639
00:48:09,854 --> 00:48:11,789
- Please get under the umbrellas.
- It's really pouring.

640
00:49:27,798 --> 00:49:29,200
Ba-ra.

641
00:49:29,433 --> 00:49:30,534
Jjanji.

642
00:49:34,472 --> 00:49:35,439
YONG-JUNG

643
00:49:41,846 --> 00:49:44,215
<i>The caller is unavailable.</i>
<i>Please record your message...</i>

644
00:50:07,638 --> 00:50:08,539
Oh my gosh!

645
00:50:27,424 --> 00:50:28,626
I figured you'd be here.

646
00:50:31,262 --> 00:50:34,431
So you two didn't come together?

647
00:50:35,399 --> 00:50:37,535
It was raining too hard,
so we cut our round short.

648
00:50:37,968 --> 00:50:40,104
I was more startled by your scream.

649
00:50:40,604 --> 00:50:43,641
I've always been scared of the rain.

650
00:50:45,309 --> 00:50:46,310
You're scared of the rain?

651
00:50:47,278 --> 00:50:48,112
Yes.

652
00:50:51,048 --> 00:50:52,049
What can I get you?

653
00:50:52,116 --> 00:50:52,983
Sparkling water.

654
00:50:53,984 --> 00:50:54,818
Me too.

655
00:50:57,087 --> 00:50:59,690
I came to make you
black bean noodles as a surprise.

656
00:51:03,427 --> 00:51:04,261
Where's Jjanji?

657
00:51:04,862 --> 00:51:05,696
The living room.

658
00:51:06,330 --> 00:51:07,164
He's not there.

659
00:51:07,831 --> 00:51:09,567
- Jjanji.
- Jjanji!

660
00:51:09,633 --> 00:51:10,668
Jjanji!

661
00:51:11,168 --> 00:51:13,103
- Jjanji!
- Jjanji!

662
00:51:21,078 --> 00:51:22,212
Jjanji!

663
00:51:27,685 --> 00:51:28,519
Oh, no.

664
00:51:32,189 --> 00:51:33,524
Dogs are scared of thunder.

665
00:51:34,525 --> 00:51:35,526
Was Carrie the same?

666
00:51:36,360 --> 00:51:38,228
That chihuahua James used to have.

667
00:51:39,063 --> 00:51:40,598
- Wasn't its name Oiji?
- Yeah.

668
00:51:41,532 --> 00:51:42,366
Are you hungry?

669
00:51:42,967 --> 00:51:43,801
I'm starving.

670
00:51:44,468 --> 00:51:45,603
Why don't you eat with us, sir?

671
00:51:45,669 --> 00:51:47,638
We're all friends here.
Don't be so formal.

672
00:51:49,573 --> 00:51:51,575
Just give me a minute while I finish up.

673
00:51:52,142 --> 00:51:53,510
- Anything I can help with?
- It's fine.

674
00:51:56,647 --> 00:51:58,315
Hire a live-in housekeeper.

675
00:51:58,382 --> 00:51:59,283
I wouldn't like that.

676
00:52:01,619 --> 00:52:02,453
Here.

677
00:52:04,355 --> 00:52:06,156
My dad's friend
has a traditional medicine clinic.

678
00:52:06,991 --> 00:52:10,594
Before passing the clinic down to his son,
he made this tonic with the finest herbs.

679
00:52:10,661 --> 00:52:12,129
I don't take herbal medicine, so...

680
00:52:12,196 --> 00:52:14,632
Still, he went to the trouble
of making this for you.

681
00:52:15,132 --> 00:52:17,234
- I don't need it.
- And I do?

682
00:52:17,434 --> 00:52:18,268
Just take it.

683
00:52:18,869 --> 00:52:21,205
It's got all kinds of precious herbs.

684
00:52:21,271 --> 00:52:23,107
You said you liked this watch, right?

685
00:52:23,173 --> 00:52:24,308
I bought one too.

686
00:52:24,775 --> 00:52:25,843
How'd you manage to get one?

687
00:52:26,176 --> 00:52:28,479
It was easy. You got one.

688
00:52:28,545 --> 00:52:29,813
LET THE DUEL BEGIN

689
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:34,244
That smells amazing!

690
00:53:34,311 --> 00:53:35,145
Come and sit.

691
00:53:35,713 --> 00:53:36,880
This looks legit.

692
00:53:36,947 --> 00:53:38,082
I can't guarantee the taste.

693
00:53:48,158 --> 00:53:49,293
The rain stopped.

694
00:53:49,626 --> 00:53:50,794
It was pouring so hard.

695
00:53:52,529 --> 00:53:54,064
It must have been hard to cook this.

696
00:53:54,131 --> 00:53:54,998
It was nothing.

697
00:53:59,436 --> 00:54:01,872
This is way better than the hotel ones.
It's not too sweet.

698
00:54:03,006 --> 00:54:04,575
Jjanji, go eat your food.

699
00:54:05,743 --> 00:54:08,378
Did you get the recipe online
or from a chef?

700
00:54:08,712 --> 00:54:10,647
It's my own recipe, just how I like it.

701
00:54:10,714 --> 00:54:11,849
The Ba-ra special?

702
00:54:13,383 --> 00:54:15,185
I wanted to find a way to thank you.

703
00:54:15,853 --> 00:54:16,854
So, a humble meal.

704
00:54:17,221 --> 00:54:18,188
Thank me for what?

705
00:54:18,255 --> 00:54:20,791
For that fancy belated birthday dinner.

706
00:54:21,358 --> 00:54:22,626
I didn't cook it.

707
00:54:22,693 --> 00:54:24,228
Even if your housekeeper did,

708
00:54:24,294 --> 00:54:25,929
it's the thought that counts.

709
00:54:27,631 --> 00:54:29,533
Can women take that tonic?

710
00:54:30,567 --> 00:54:31,869
It's specifically for men.

711
00:54:32,936 --> 00:54:34,738
This is good enough to sell.
I'll help you do it.

712
00:54:38,809 --> 00:54:39,743
Hello?

713
00:54:40,410 --> 00:54:41,645
<i>Hi, Jae-im.</i>

714
00:54:41,712 --> 00:54:42,646
Hey.

715
00:54:43,180 --> 00:54:45,015
Could I get an MRI scan?

716
00:54:45,549 --> 00:54:47,284
Why? Are you not feeling well?

717
00:54:47,484 --> 00:54:48,552
I'm a little dizzy.

718
00:54:48,852 --> 00:54:49,686
Is it bad?

719
00:54:50,287 --> 00:54:51,288
How bad is it?

720
00:54:51,355 --> 00:54:52,790
It's not that bad.

721
00:54:52,856 --> 00:54:54,691
I just had a headache a couple days ago.

722
00:54:54,858 --> 00:54:56,794
We're fully booked,
so if I squeeze you in,

723
00:54:57,294 --> 00:54:59,429
it has to be early morning or late night.

724
00:54:59,496 --> 00:55:01,431
I prefer early mornings.

725
00:55:01,498 --> 00:55:03,634
All right. Let me check and text you back.

726
00:55:03,700 --> 00:55:04,535
Thank you.

727
00:55:06,870 --> 00:55:08,372
It's probably nothing serious.

728
00:55:08,739 --> 00:55:10,941
If he'd burst a blood vessel
or had a stroke,

729
00:55:11,008 --> 00:55:12,176
the headache would be excruciating.

730
00:55:13,043 --> 00:55:14,778
He can be a bit of a hypochondriac.

731
00:55:15,045 --> 00:55:15,879
That's a good thing.

732
00:55:18,682 --> 00:55:19,616
Is this a cocktail?

733
00:55:19,683 --> 00:55:21,018
It's nothing fancy.

734
00:55:29,726 --> 00:55:30,694
There's wine in it.

735
00:55:31,128 --> 00:55:32,496
Wine and two other things.

736
00:55:32,763 --> 00:55:33,831
It's not bad.

737
00:55:35,432 --> 00:55:38,435
Since you don't have your housekeeper,
and the house was empty,

738
00:55:38,502 --> 00:55:39,670
I wanted to surprise you.

739
00:55:39,736 --> 00:55:41,271
- Did it work?
- Absolutely.

740
00:55:42,005 --> 00:55:42,840
Thank you.

741
00:55:43,473 --> 00:55:44,474
Let me finish yours.

742
00:55:48,345 --> 00:55:49,947
You'll get drunk if you chug it.

743
00:55:50,013 --> 00:55:51,248
That's for lightweights.

744
00:55:52,149 --> 00:55:54,651
Please, don't force yourself
if you don't like it.

745
00:55:58,388 --> 00:55:59,256
Leave the dishes.

746
00:56:00,190 --> 00:56:01,391
They're already in the dishwasher.

747
00:56:01,925 --> 00:56:02,926
Let's go grocery shopping.

748
00:56:06,663 --> 00:56:08,098
NUA CHILDREN'S HOME MANAGER

749
00:56:12,302 --> 00:56:13,871
- It's me.
- Yes, Dr. Shin.

750
00:56:14,171 --> 00:56:15,772
Send me the files on Geum Ba-ra.

751
00:56:16,306 --> 00:56:17,374
All of it.

752
00:56:17,441 --> 00:56:18,609
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

753
00:57:14,097 --> 00:57:16,633
We'll run the scan,
but I doubt we'll find anything.

754
00:57:16,700 --> 00:57:18,201
That'd be a relief.

755
00:57:19,803 --> 00:57:21,038
Take this after the scan.

756
00:57:21,905 --> 00:57:23,140
- Tonics?
- Yes.

757
00:57:23,740 --> 00:57:26,009
I also gave some to Yong-jung,
so this is all yours.

758
00:57:26,076 --> 00:57:27,244
Thank you very much.

759
00:57:27,577 --> 00:57:29,513
How'd you know I like herbal tonics?

760
00:57:29,713 --> 00:57:32,916
I'm sorry to make a fuss
and have you come to my home

761
00:57:32,983 --> 00:57:34,751
on your rare day off.

762
00:57:45,395 --> 00:57:46,263
Hello.

763
00:57:46,897 --> 00:57:47,798
A pregnancy test, please.

764
00:57:54,171 --> 00:57:55,205
That'll be 5,000 won.

765
00:58:08,285 --> 00:58:10,320
What was Ju-sin doing in the kitchen?

766
00:58:12,189 --> 00:58:14,491
He just hugged me because I screamed.

767
00:58:14,992 --> 00:58:16,927
He was probably very annoyed.

768
00:58:18,829 --> 00:58:20,297
I freaked out too.

769
00:58:20,364 --> 00:58:21,798
I thought it was you.

770
00:58:21,865 --> 00:58:22,933
Are you that scared of rain?

771
00:58:23,633 --> 00:58:26,570
I'm scared of heavy rain
with thunder and lightning.

772
00:58:27,571 --> 00:58:29,206
What do you do when you're alone then?

773
00:58:29,940 --> 00:58:31,074
I just endure it.

774
00:58:31,975 --> 00:58:33,477
Isn't that bad for your heart?

775
00:58:34,277 --> 00:58:36,246
Don't you need to go check on Mr. Ha?

776
00:58:36,713 --> 00:58:38,348
I will, after I drop you off.

777
00:58:39,583 --> 00:58:40,417
Yong-jung.

778
00:58:41,018 --> 00:58:43,620
Mr. Ha told me to call him by his name,

779
00:58:44,121 --> 00:58:45,188
but I just can't.

780
00:58:47,657 --> 00:58:48,959
Then don't force yourself.

781
00:58:50,527 --> 00:58:52,996
Don't force yourself for Ju-sin either.

782
00:58:53,563 --> 00:58:54,664
Of course not.

783
00:58:54,731 --> 00:58:56,133
Dr. Shin wouldn't stand for it.

784
00:58:57,100 --> 00:58:59,870
All the kids at the orphanage
adored Dr. Shin,

785
00:59:00,370 --> 00:59:01,505
especially Jin-ju.

786
00:59:02,506 --> 00:59:04,541
He had such an incredible presence.

787
00:59:04,908 --> 00:59:06,443
- Ju-sin?
- Yeah.

788
00:59:09,980 --> 00:59:10,814
What about me?

789
00:59:12,549 --> 00:59:14,618
You're warm and down-to-earth.

790
00:59:15,285 --> 00:59:16,787
Which would you prefer,
presence or warmth?

791
00:59:18,522 --> 00:59:20,590
People are more drawn to that human side.

792
00:59:21,058 --> 00:59:21,892
At least, I am.

793
00:59:24,061 --> 00:59:25,195
Jjanji's probably waiting.

794
00:59:25,262 --> 00:59:26,129
Let's take this to go.

795
00:59:27,130 --> 00:59:29,900
You're such a good cook,

796
00:59:30,567 --> 00:59:31,968
but your fridge is totally empty.

797
00:59:33,437 --> 00:59:34,871
Thank you for all this food.

798
00:59:40,811 --> 00:59:41,812
Let's go, Jjanji.

799
00:59:52,255 --> 00:59:56,026
ELEMENTARY STUDENT RECORD

800
00:59:58,728 --> 01:00:00,730
2ND SEMESTER TYPING CONTEST:
GOLD MEDAL

801
01:00:00,797 --> 01:00:02,766
FIRE SAFETY DRAWING CONTEST:
EXCELLENCE

802
01:00:02,833 --> 01:00:04,935
PAPER AIRPLANE THROWING CONTEST:
GOLD MEDAL

803
01:00:08,271 --> 01:00:09,106
I'm sorry.

804
01:00:13,643 --> 01:00:15,245
For the sake of Jin-ju's future,

805
01:00:16,246 --> 01:00:18,748
we've agreed to say
that she annulled the adoption.

806
01:00:19,816 --> 01:00:20,884
Don't let on that you know.

807
01:00:21,485 --> 01:00:23,420
I'll tell the orphanage manager the truth

808
01:00:24,187 --> 01:00:25,388
and clear your name.

809
01:00:43,240 --> 01:00:44,307
Hey, Yong-jung.

810
01:00:44,374 --> 01:00:46,943
<i>One of your best qualities</i>
<i>is that you always pick up right away.</i>

811
01:00:47,777 --> 01:00:48,845
It's funny.

812
01:00:48,912 --> 01:00:51,114
You only seem to call
when I can actually pick up.

813
01:00:51,848 --> 01:00:52,916
<i>Can we video call?</i>

814
01:00:53,316 --> 01:00:54,151
Yeah.

815
01:00:57,954 --> 01:00:59,956
<i>- Call his name.</i>
- Jjanji.

816
01:01:00,023 --> 01:01:02,526
<i>What's that sound? Where's Ba-ra?</i>

817
01:01:04,127 --> 01:01:04,995
<i>He doesn't care.</i>

818
01:01:05,328 --> 01:01:06,796
Jjanji looks totally drained.

819
01:01:07,264 --> 01:01:08,398
I wore him out.

820
01:01:08,598 --> 01:01:10,400
You have too much stamina.

821
01:01:10,734 --> 01:01:13,069
<i>It's 9kg versus over 70kg, right?</i>

822
01:01:13,136 --> 01:01:14,304
I'm 75kg.

823
01:01:14,371 --> 01:01:15,305
<i>Is that even a fair fight?</i>

824
01:01:16,039 --> 01:01:17,774
Have you showered already?

825
01:01:18,408 --> 01:01:19,276
<i>I was about to.</i>

826
01:01:19,809 --> 01:01:21,278
There's nothing to hide.

827
01:01:21,344 --> 01:01:22,279
You look beautiful.

828
01:01:22,746 --> 01:01:24,414
<i>One of your many great qualities.</i>

829
01:01:24,848 --> 01:01:25,949
<i>Your endless compliments.</i>

830
01:01:26,016 --> 01:01:27,450
I'm just telling the truth.

831
01:01:28,919 --> 01:01:29,753
<i>Hey.</i>

832
01:01:30,086 --> 01:01:32,155
- What is it?
<i>- He's peeing while staring at me.</i>

833
01:01:33,623 --> 01:01:34,457
<i>Are you jealous?</i>

834
01:01:35,392 --> 01:01:36,393
- I gotta go.
<i>- Okay.</i>

835
01:01:39,162 --> 01:01:40,497
Who is that? It's late.

836
01:01:40,564 --> 01:01:42,132
<i>I don't know. Let me hang up for a sec.</i>

837
01:01:42,432 --> 01:01:43,633
- No, don't hang up.
<i>- Okay.</i>

838
01:01:48,338 --> 01:01:50,073
<i>It's Momo. I gotta go.</i>

839
01:01:50,807 --> 01:01:51,641
Okay.

840
01:02:03,286 --> 01:02:05,088
I didn't come here to hear you say no.

841
01:02:10,160 --> 01:02:12,495
Wouldn't it be better
to hire another assistant?

842
01:02:12,562 --> 01:02:14,731
What if they spread rumors
or post my life online?

843
01:02:16,333 --> 01:02:18,368
How can you trust someone you don't know?

844
01:02:22,639 --> 01:02:23,807
Who were you drinking with?

845
01:02:27,210 --> 01:02:28,178
Now...

846
01:02:28,845 --> 01:02:31,748
You're the only one
I can trust and depend on.

847
01:02:45,028 --> 01:02:46,830
PREGNANCY TEST

848
01:03:06,616 --> 01:03:08,485
- Hello?
<i>- Is the party over?</i>

849
01:03:09,719 --> 01:03:11,421
Yes, I'm back.

850
01:03:11,488 --> 01:03:13,056
<i>Nurse Park will be there in 20 minutes.</i>

851
01:03:13,590 --> 01:03:14,424
<i>Go with him.</i>

852
01:03:30,540 --> 01:03:31,875
Where are we going?

853
01:04:11,715 --> 01:04:12,682
Did you have fun?

854
01:04:14,050 --> 01:04:14,884
It was okay.

855
01:04:18,421 --> 01:04:19,255
From the garden.

856
01:04:30,133 --> 01:04:31,768
When will you stop licking your lips?

857
01:04:34,537 --> 01:04:35,672
Right away.

858
01:04:35,739 --> 01:04:36,940
I won't do it again.

859
01:05:54,083 --> 01:05:56,085
I can't let an old man
go to the hospital alone.

860
01:05:56,152 --> 01:05:56,986
Geez.

861
01:06:02,826 --> 01:06:06,629
A young person was looking down
on a middle-aged Madam.

862
01:06:06,963 --> 01:06:09,632
So the Madam said, "I know about youth
because I was young once."

863
01:06:09,699 --> 01:06:11,000
"But have you ever been old?"

864
01:06:11,067 --> 01:06:13,903
"I have. So don't be a smartass."

865
01:06:14,604 --> 01:06:16,873
Getting worked up like that
just proves that you're old.

866
01:06:28,451 --> 01:06:30,787
RADIOLOGY

867
01:06:53,309 --> 01:06:54,978
How would you feel about a brain change?

868
01:06:58,348 --> 01:06:59,616
Have you ever thought about it?

869
01:07:01,784 --> 01:07:02,619
No.

870
01:07:04,087 --> 01:07:08,124
I heard that soon,
AI could replace a whole human brain.

871
01:07:12,028 --> 01:07:13,229
What if you could keep your face

872
01:07:14,397 --> 01:07:16,032
and just change your brain?

873
01:07:24,641 --> 01:07:25,708
Are you saying...

874
01:07:27,443 --> 01:07:28,645
you can do that?

875
01:07:45,295 --> 01:07:46,396
If it were possible...

876
01:07:49,332 --> 01:07:50,466
who would I swap with?

877
01:08:34,477 --> 01:08:37,347
DOCTOR SHIN

878
01:08:37,413 --> 01:08:38,548
Oh my goodness.

879
01:08:38,615 --> 01:08:39,782
- Congratulations.
- For what?

880
01:08:40,216 --> 01:08:43,720
<i>What if you could keep your face</i>
<i>and just change your brain?</i>

881
01:08:43,786 --> 01:08:46,055
<i>Are you saying you can do that?</i>

882
01:08:46,122 --> 01:08:48,157
- Do you trust people?
- You have to at first.

883
01:08:48,224 --> 01:08:50,560
- But I don't want to be betrayed.
- And if they do?

884
01:08:50,994 --> 01:08:52,929
- How do you know her?
- I'm her father.

885
01:08:52,996 --> 01:08:54,797
<i>I have the upper hand now, don't I?</i>

886
01:08:55,031 --> 01:08:56,566
So I'm all washed up now?

887
01:08:56,633 --> 01:08:57,900
I didn't know you talked like that.

888
01:08:57,967 --> 01:08:59,068
Don't change the subject.

889
01:08:59,135 --> 01:09:00,269
What's your type?

890
01:09:00,336 --> 01:09:01,871
- You should go.
- What if I don't want to?

891
01:09:01,938 --> 01:09:03,373
I know you're just being polite.

892
01:09:03,439 --> 01:09:04,440
I really mean it.

893
01:09:06,075 --> 01:09:08,011
<i>How dare you lie to me?</i>

894
01:09:08,678 --> 01:09:09,646
Lie?

895
01:09:10,713 --> 01:09:11,714
Why would I?

896
01:09:11,781 --> 01:09:13,316
How could you just sit there
eating strawberries?

897
01:09:13,916 --> 01:09:14,851
Like it's nothing?

898
01:09:14,917 --> 01:09:15,752
Yes.

899
01:09:15,818 --> 01:09:18,588
I must be low on vitamin C,
because they're absolutely delicious.

900
01:09:19,689 --> 01:09:21,758
<i>Give me back my brain! My brain!</i>

901
01:09:23,926 --> 01:09:26,496
<i>Mr. Shin Ju-sin, you're under arrest</i>
<i>for the murder of Kim Jin-ju.</i>

902
01:09:29,966 --> 01:09:31,901
Subtitle translation by Kim Moo-kyeong
